⭐⭐⭐⭐⭐ Question 84/120 – End-to-End JSON Interview Challenge

🎤 Interview Question

You receive employee records from Kafka in the following format:

{
  "emp_id":101,
  "employee":{
      "name":"John",
      "department":"IT",
      "skills":["Python","Spark","SQL"]
  }
}

Write PySpark code to:

1. Parse the JSON.


2. Flatten the employee details.


3. Explode the skills array.


4. Display one row per employee skill.




---

📊 Expected Output

emp_id	name	department	skill

101	John	IT	Python
101	John	IT	Spark
101	John	IT	SQL



---

✅ Recommended Solution

from pyspark.sql.functions import from_json, explode, col
from pyspark.sql.types import *

schema = StructType([
    StructField("emp_id", IntegerType()),
    StructField(
        "employee",
        StructType([
            StructField("name", StringType()),
            StructField("department", StringType()),
            StructField("skills", ArrayType(StringType()))
        ])
    )
])

parsed_df = df.withColumn(
    "json_data",
    from_json(col("value"), schema)
)

result = parsed_df.select(
    "json_data.emp_id",
    "json_data.employee.name",
    "json_data.employee.department",
    explode("json_data.employee.skills").alias("skill")
)

result.show()


