⭐⭐⭐⭐⭐ Question 101/120 – Predicate Pushdown

🎤 Interview Question

You have a Parquet file containing 100 million employee records.

You need only employees whose salary is greater than 50,000.

How do you optimize the read?


---

✅ Recommended Solution

df = (
    spark.read.parquet("/employee")
         .filter("salary > 50000")
)

> If the file format supports it (Parquet/ORC), Spark pushes the filter down to the storage layer and reads only the required data.




---

🎤 Most Asked Interview Questions

Q1. What is Predicate Pushdown?

Answer

Spark pushes filter conditions to the data source so unnecessary rows are not read.


---

Q2. Which file formats support Predicate Pushdown?

Answer

Parquet

ORC

Many JDBC sources (depending on the database)



---

Q3. Why is Predicate Pushdown important?

Answer

It reduces disk I/O, memory usage, and query execution time.


